item.title: CVE-2024-22460|2024-05-08T15:52:17.721Z -- Dell -- Data Manager Appliance Software (DMAS)
item.description: Dell PowerProtect DM5500 version 5.15.0.0 and prior contains an insecure deserialization Vulnerability. A remote attacker with high privileges could potentially exploit this vulnerability, leading to arbitrary code execution on the vulnerable application.

item.title: CVE-2024-24908|2024-05-08T15:48:07.079Z -- Dell -- Data Manager Appliance Software (DMAS)
item.description: Dell PowerProtect DM5500 version 5.15.0.0 and prior contain an Arbitrary File Delete via Path Traversal vulnerability. A remote attacker with high privileges could potentially exploit this vulnerability to deletion of arbitrary files stored on the server filesystem.
